centre: Vulnerabilities and opportunities in the East Asia came out as the most important issue related to climate change. 37.50 per cent responses endorsed this issue. The second highest responses were for a vision of Human Development through a low carbon society and 28.13 per cent responses towards that point. Some respondents also voted for Making the low carbon society a reality: going beyond the adaptation\u2010mitigation dichotomy (21.88 per cent of responses) and for mapping and measuring human development from a climate change perspective in the East Asia (9.38 per cent of responses) (Table 5). \u2022 29.73 per cent responses favoured participating in network discussions for", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4d1cd6d2-5d40-4940-8dc8-7313e478db92": {"__data__": {"id_": "4d1cd6d2-5d40-4940-8dc8-7313e478db92", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-climate-change-asia-stakeholders-consultation-report", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report on Climate Change: Asia Stakeholders Consultation Report", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-climate-change-asia-stakeholders-consultation-report", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c4449c4e3454b75f0dfa081902e3b63a54a9dfae4c3edc69d9e75eb7b4c02782"}, "3": {"node_id": "1a52cd1c-cb30-413b-aae0-7c07155bb0aa", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia